 <h3>

     <span style="color:#000000;">Tutorial Suggestion</span>
 </h3>
   
 </div>



<div class="details" >
    <div class="vtbegenerated"> 
 <p><br><span><span></span> Tutorials provide and excellent opportunity for active learning and peer learning.<span></span></span><span><span></span> You should</span><span>t be prepared and ready <span></span></span><span><span></span></span><span><span></span></span><span><span></span></span><span>before the tutorials.<span></span></span><span><span></span> Get to know what will be discussed.<span></span></span><span><span></span> Work in groups of <span></span></span><span><span></span>4</span><span><span></span>-</span><span><span></span>6</span><span><span></span> people and present/discuss your solutions to the class.<span></span></span><span><span></span> </span></p> 
</div>

  </div>

 <div id="_1919879_1previewModule" class="moduleSample">
 </div>
</li>




<li id="contentListItem:_1919880_1"	class="clearfix liItem read">


<div class="item clearfix" ID="_1919880_1">

 <h3>
  <span class="reorder editmode hideme"><span><img src="https://learn.blackboardcdn.com/3800.9.0-rel.25+4afe1a1/images/ci/icons/generic_updown.gif" alt="" /></span></span>



     <span style="color:#000000;">Tutorial Instructions</span>
 </h3>
   
 </div>



<div class="details" >
    <div class="vtbegenerated"> 
 <p><br><span><span></span><span><span></span>1.<span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span> In Tutorial <span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span>#</span><span></span><span><span></span>1</span><span></span><span><span></span>,</span><span></span><span><span></span> please form working groups/teams of <span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span>4</span><span></span><span><span></span>-</span><span></span><span><span></span>6</span><span></span><span><span></span> people with one group per table.<span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span> Stay in these groups for the whole of the semester during your tutorial sessions.<span></span></span><span></span></span></p> 
 <p><span><span></span><span><span></span>2.<span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span> Your active <span></span></span><span>participation during the tutorial sessions <span></span></span><span><span></span></span><span><span></span></span><span><span></span></span><span><span></span></span><span>will help you to understand topics and solutions better</span><span>.</span></span></p> 
 <p><span><span></span><span><span></span>3.<span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span> You should review relevant lecture material and notes <span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span>(see Topic Plan)<span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span> before each tutorial and be ready to discuss your ideas to the solutions o<span><span>f</span></span> the tutorial questions during the tutorial sessions.<span></span></span><span></span></span></p> 
 <p><span><span></span><span><span></span>4.<span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span> Each tutorial may start with one or more individual or team readiness questions covering basic concepts relevant to the topic of the tutorial.<span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span> Your tutor will make sure that everybody has equal opportunity to answer/discuss the readiness questions in the tutorials throughout the course.<span></span></span><span></span></span></p> 
 <p><span><span></span><span><span></span>5.<span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span> At the end of each tutorial,<span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span> the tutor may select 1</span><span></span><span></span><span><span></span> or 2</span><span></span><span></span><span><span></span> groups/teams and assign the questions of the next tutorial to the selected groups.The selected groups should prepare solutions for the assigned questions. In the next tutorial,<span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span> the selected working groups will present*<span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span> their solutions to the class.<span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span> The tutor will lead discussion on the presented solutions,<span></span></span><span></span><span><span></span> and possibly present his solution</span><span style="color: #ff0000;"><span><span></span>*</span></span><span style="color: #ff0000;"><span><span></span>*</span></span><span></span><span><span></span> if necessary.<span></span></span><span></span></span></p> 
 <p><span><span></span><span><span></span><em>* Do not simply reuse the solutions from past semesters.</em></span><em></em><span><em> You must be able to explain your solutions and be ready to contribute your opinions/ideas with the tutor and the classmates.</em><span></span></span><span></span></span></p> 
 <p><span><span></span><span style="color: #ff0000;"><span><span></span>**<span></span></span></span><span style="color: #ff0000;"></span><span><span></span> </span><span style="color: #ff0000;"><em><span>The tutor’s solutions do not mean <span></span></span></em></span><span style="color: #ff0000;"><em><span><span></span>“model”<span></span></span><span><span></span> or <span></span></span><span><span></span>“standard”<span></span></span><span><span></span> solutions.<span></span></span><span><span></span> In the context of software engineering,<span></span></span></em></span><span style="color: #ff0000;"><em><span><span></span> we rarely have model or standard solution. <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Therefore there will not be such solutions posted on NTULearn after each tutorial session</strong></span>.</span></em></span><span><span></span> </span><span></span></span></p> 
 <p><br></p> 
</div>
